text:
today marks three years since i was raped. i didn’t realize that until midway through the morning, which is significant, and i’ve talked about my own experience with sexual assault a lot, so i’m going to talk about something different; what happened to me is not unique. it’s not rare, or abnormal, or an outlier. my story is one of many, each with their own gut-wrenching details, their own long battles back, and what makes these stories so powerful is that there are so fucking many of them.
.
1 in 4. 1 in 6. for men the statistics range from 1 in 33 to 1 in 70, and it’s probably much more than that; for every ten rape survivors, there is one man.
.
these numbers increase for people who are marginalized; 49% of multiracial women, 45% of native american women, and over 20% have been the victims of sexual violence; 1 in 2 trans people have been sexually assaulted.
.
1 in 4 girls and 1 in 6 boys will be the victims of sexual contact before they turn eighteen.
.
30% of women who have been sexually assaulted will show signs of ptsd for more than nine months after the assault.
.
the cost of being raped is about $130,000.
.
my story is a very old and awful one. it is not unique. look around next time you’re in a room with other people, and count out groups of four women. think of your friends, your classmates, your family. groups of four. how many of them have had to bear something unbearable? how many of them have their own awful story?
•
•
•
•
#sexualassault #survivors #1in4 #metoo #metoomovement

text:
i constantly get women message me, wanting to start their own business, but not having the confidence in themselves to 'just say yes'! they tell me they're not inspiring, they don't know enough people, they don't have time, etc etc. 🙈

when i look back before i started my business, i didn’t have many close friends. i rarely posted on facebook and when i did it was mainly doom and gloom! 😳 (the cringe of looking at my ‘memories’ 😂) the beauty of this business is you learn as you go along, i'm still learning and people who have done this a lot longer than me still learn new things! you make new friends as you go and you have so much fun doing it that you will make the time for it! 
i rarely write long winded posts... but i just needed to get it off my chest. have some faith in yourselves and you can achieve anything you put your mind to. look at donald trump! 😂

good night! 🙌🏼

text:
hi. this is me. this is another photo of me screaming at the world, acting touch, climbing uphill, concuring the elements. people (read: men) often ask me why i become so passionate when i talk about being a woman in this world, or when i write shows about female heroes in history like kenau, iphigeneia or margaret hughes. ‘why are you so angry? go get married, have some kids and shut up! smile, girl, you’re far too pretty to be angry.’ i’m not angry in this picture. i’m just showing my teeth. why? because i have to. why? because even a spoilt, entitled, privileged uptown white girl like me has had her #metoo moments and has to fight to be taken seriously in business or has to answer for the fact that she travels alone, goes to bars alone, drinks pints of black beer and didn’t start a family yet. so sometimes girls like me have to pound our chest like a gorilla and show our teeth to show the world that the fact that we don’t fit into a box doesn’t mean that we are freaks. last week a date asked if i was sure i wasn’t gay because i was so different from all the women he knew. what is gender anyway? 
this post isn’t about me. the most impressive moment in my trip to scotland was watching hannah gadsby’s show on netflix. watch it. it’s important. this woman will change the way you look at the world. at women. at gender. at being gay. it will change the way you raise your children and it will help you understand that we, as people, have to do a better job at understanding each other and allowing everybody be who they are, no more labels, no more phobia, no more boxes. it will show you an amazing, inspiring, strong, vulnarable, angry woman who has been broken and who has built herself up again. it will hit you like a ton of bricks. it will open your eyes. my sister has been asking me to watch it for weeks and i was ‘too busy’ watching a stupid netflix show. no excuses. watch it. 
and us women: let’s show our teeth when we need to, but also be kind and empowering towards each other. let everybody love who they want to love and identify with whatever gender and let’s lift each other up instead of putting each other down. we still have a long way to go.

el silbato como arma femenina contra el acoso sexual, una idea surgida hace dos años en la capital de méxico, ha dado el salto hasta marruecos, donde un grupo de activistas repartieron hoy cerca de 10.000 silbatos por todo el país para animar a las mujeres a silbar ante cada caso de ataque.

la versión marroquí del #metoo se llama #masaktach (no me callo) y surgió hace unos meses en las redes sociales. son sus activistas las que hoy se lanzaron a las calles de todo el país para repartir los silbatos con el lema “si se sobrepasa, pita”. “no se trata de una manifestación ni de una marcha”, dijo a efe una de las fundadoras del movimiento, leyla slassi, sino de sensibilizar y “literalmente hacer ruido” para atajar un fenómeno que “está ahí, en todo momento y en todo lugar”. las transeúntes que hoy eran abordadas en las avenidas céntricas de rabat mostraban en un principio su sorpresa ante el inesperado “regalo” de un silbato, y se lo tomaban en un principio a broma, hasta que, tras una breve conversación, entendían la filosofía de la acción y aceptaban llevarse su silbato.

uno de los mensajes que repetían las activistas era la propia ley 503-1-1 del código penal marroquí, que castiga con penas de entre uno y seis meses de cárcel más una multa a quien practique el acoso “en espacios públicos y otros con actos, palabras y gestos de carácter sexual o con fines sexuales”. la ley, que acaba de aprobarse recientemente, ha tenido un recorrido hasta ahora discreto, y el primer juicio celebrado en la ciudad de fez contra un acosador para aplicarle esa nueva ley acabó en nada, pues la víctima retiró su denuncia ante la atención mediática levantada por el caso.

el movimiento feminista lamenta que esa ley, pese a su contenido positivo, no contemple mecanismos concretos que hagan más fáciles las denuncias, ni tampoco incluya sensibilización entre los policías y los jueces, encargados de aplicar esa ley.

text:
grateful to have spoken at the #metoo event as a latinx transmasculine sexual abuse survivor. 
i first experienced sexual abuse at 13, i would wear baggy clothes to hide my unwanted puberty changes. an adult (white cis man) took advantage of my dysphoria and befriended me and then took advantage of the situation. he forced me to do things i couldn’t comprehend, that made me feel dirty. his excuse was that he was curious to see what my “true “ sex was under my baggy clothes. 
the next time was when i was 18, i had started my self discovery journey to transition, had cut my hair and started dressing more masculine,  i was sexually harassed by an intoxicated man, who told me i was too “pretty” to dress like a boy, that i needed to try boys, then went on to call me names. this was on a metro bus with a lot of people, yet not one spoke up. he then went on to get off the bus on my stop and stalk me until i went to a coffee shop to wait it out. 
i spoke up at this event, to offer a voice in the trans community who faces the most abuse. 
in fact “one in two transgender individuals are sexually abused or assaulted at some point in their lives. some reports estimate that transgender survivors may experience rates of sexual assault up to 66 percent, often coupled with physical assaults or abuse.” i am visible for those that cannot be, i am visible so that my trans siblings know that they are not alone.

text_retweet:
slacktivism: are we lazy?
as you are reading this post, a politician is calling us lazy. there is evidence of gen-z and millennials being the age gap that votes the least! a term called slacktivism has been coined to describe our actions or rather lack thereof. we [internet-users] receive our news through social media platforms and repost pressing issues through hashtag activism. by doing so, we can get these topics trending globally and raise awareness to issues that affect our daily lives. our participation does matter, whether it be online or voting. this stigma has been present in our generation, but we can utilize these powerful digital tools in order to create change. #youmatter

text: been starting holiday shopping early this year & when necessary hiding it with a danger dragon on guard [aka tiny snek, mercury] for morgan’s pressies. because my teenager is wicked smart & will find them. i try to leave magic in this & thusly, my local artisan haunts in the day to day allow for the gradual ease & enjoyment. it’s been years that the shopping season hasn’t completely repulsed me & i steer clear of it. that sometimes spills into the mood overall & coupled with history - i dread holidays. time heals & as we make clear of that - we make new traditions. one, is in what we spend on & where. i’ve always been a creator & gifted from this, but it’s a great addition in the community of online artists through fb & ig. it’s important to support each other & our good vibe tribes (s.o., smallish bears, birdos, cattos & doggos). i’m proud of my artist friends who work into the ether to hone their craft & survive on their wares. it’s not an easy choice & the tax changes this year are gonna be brutal. keep going. i am grateful that i can trade work, have the time for commissions that mean a great deal to them & in the creation of to me, too. a huge contrast to how i felt under corporate pressured rules of financial benefit over those we served. i sleep better at night & that this is carried into my choices for this season, as it should; reciprocal in the spirit of giving. a palpable energy in this; it’s a web that i can connect to. it grounds me in what is important when the world feels anything but & it gives me hope in today & for tomorrow. i learned today of how this is not limited to these walls. this tee from @billsafi is mine. 😍i wore it out shopping today, & i began to make note of people smiling at me - which is nice, but why? i happened to catch the gaze of a woman in line & then i got it. i am gonna say it - i looked for it after. wonders of positivity in the following places/peoples especially the faces of women reading it & the smile grow when it hit home. best part of art. ☺️✨my 2 favorite ladysmiths are around my neck (every day)turquoise ‘ancestors’ skull by @floraandfauuna & the ‘evil eye monocle’ by @flannerygrace

text:
jämställdhetsresan fortsätter
resan inleddes med en enkät till föreningens ledare, styrelse, aktiva och föräldrar. redan på tågresan upp till stockholm i torsdags 8 nov började arbetet med att utifrån enkäten sätta föreningens nuläge av sammi, nagham, mortaza och margareth. arbetet fortsatte med att ta fram de problem föreningen vill lösa som mål formulerades och den konkretiserade handlingsplanen kommer tas fram tillsammans med styrelsen. 
vi representerar en idrott som innehåller våld och har varit överrepresenterat av män under många år vilket syns tydligt bland ledare och styrelse runtom i landet. idag är ändå utövandet mer jämställt med största tävlingsframgångar internationellt på damsidan. 
föreningen har nu påbörjat sin resa mot en mer jämställd förening och idrott. utmaningarna ligger bland annat i att förändra normer om kampsport, ledare och förtroendevalda. 
förutsättningarna är goda med en medlemsbas beståendes av 47% tjejer/kvinnor och 53% killar/män samt lika fördelat kvinnliga som manliga ledare. 
vi ser framemot det fortsatta arbetet. 
#metoo #jämställdhet #idrott #taekwondo #kampsport #machokultur #kampsport 
västra götalands idrottsförbund & sisu idrottsutbildarna västra götaland tillsammans med allbright, max bergander och huskurage för ett mer jämställt samhälle och idrott.

text:
🗣 digital activism panel is on nov. 17 @ 12pm. in the wake of the #metoo movement, locally-based filmmakers and artists explore the implications this may have for women and trans folks belonging to communities of colour, black communities, and indigenous communities locally, and beyond. 
meet our panelist erica violet lee! she is a graduate student in social justice education at the university of toronto. she is an indigenous feminist, community organizer from inner-city saskatoon, and a nēhiyaw philosopher queen learning how to be a writer in the wastelands. 
join the discussion & support #rpff18! the discussion will focus on how each panelist’s work engages with ideas of racialized misogyny, sexual literacy, consent, and gender-based justice.

text:
@regrann from @thedailyember - now with the progressives we elected, lets stop selling weapons to saudi arabia.
.
.
“washington (ap) — the united states will stop refueling saudi arabian aircraft fighting houthi rebels in yemen, the pentagon and the saudi kingdom said late friday.

the refueling change does not affect the u.s. military assistance and training to improve the saudi airstrikes, which have reportedly caused thousands of civilian deaths. “the u.s. and the coalition are planning to collaborate on building up legitimate yemeni forces to defend the yemeni people, secure their country’s borders, and contribute to counter al-qaida and isis efforts in yemen and the region,” u.s. defense secretary jim mattis said.

as a result, the decision to halt the u.s. refueling will likely have little impact on the fight, but will allow the trump administration to say it has taken action against the saudis for the devastation in yemen.

the saudi statement said it had “increased its capability to independently conduct inflight refueling,” and therefore “requested cessation of inflight refueling support for its operations in yemen.” the action comes amid growing congressional anger against saudi arabia, a key ally and the country where president donald trump made his first visit abroad after taking office.”
via @apnews

text:
now with the progressives we elected, lets stop selling weapons to saudi arabia.
.
.
“washington (ap) — the united states will stop refueling saudi arabian aircraft fighting houthi rebels in yemen, the pentagon and the saudi kingdom said late friday.

the refueling change does not affect the u.s. military assistance and training to improve the saudi airstrikes, which have reportedly caused thousands of civilian deaths. “the u.s. and the coalition are planning to collaborate on building up legitimate yemeni forces to defend the yemeni people, secure their country’s borders, and contribute to counter al-qaida and isis efforts in yemen and the region,” u.s. defense secretary jim mattis said.

as a result, the decision to halt the u.s. refueling will likely have little impact on the fight, but will allow the trump administration to say it has taken action against the saudis for the devastation in yemen.

the saudi statement said it had “increased its capability to independently conduct inflight refueling,” and therefore “requested cessation of inflight refueling support for its operations in yemen.” the action comes amid growing congressional anger against saudi arabia, a key ally and the country where president donald trump made his first visit abroad after taking office.”
via @apnews

text:
my sport gave me so many immeasurable opportunities. i have a bachelors and masters degree completely debt free, i have traveled to and trained in three different countries, competed in almost all 50 states, and have a resume filled with characteristics that make me a stand out applicant. but the sport also shaped me into the perfect victim - the silent survivor. it taught me that deviations from perfection are unacceptable. that  appearance sometimes matters more than skill. and that power and authority trump morals and comfort. .
.
my story traces every step of what molded me into the perfect victim for larry nassar. how gymnastics created an environment where silence was easier than the pain and discomfort. my book demands change. .
.
.

text:
sabato #10novembre una giornata di grande mobilitazione a #roma. 
la mattina a lato di piazza venezia per dire #nopillon insieme alle donne, ai movimenti femministi e alle realtà #lgbti. abbiamo urlato al governo e alla maggioranza che non siamo disposti ad alcun passo indietro sui diritti e le libertà. @possibileit era in piazza non solo nella capitale ma anche un tutte le altre manifestazioni indette in italia.

il pomeriggio un corteo affollato, rumoroso, colorato, ha invaso il centro di roma per dire no al decreto #salvini sulla sicurezza. nessuno è straniero, nessuno è illegale. la nostra unica cittadinanza è l'umanità. 
#unitiesolidali #stopracism #stopfascism #agitazionepermanente #sinistra #possibile #wetogether #metoo

text:
not inktober, day 11

veterans day, 2018 
america,

we have wronged so many people. we have wronged ourselves and one another. we have shown hatred, and we have denied ourselves.

the death of a person by another man's hand is not only a tremendous loss of life; it's also signifies the loss of our humanity. 
we must be aware of what we are capable of in order to be sensitive. what good is communicating without the ability to listen? if we disagree, not knowing how to communicate can become destructive. 
if we can have the patience to speak, to mediate rather than to dictate, we might not come to an immediate agreement, but we will at least see that we are trying. it means more than buying time.

how do we make the best of what we have? what does it mean to move forward? 
stronger together.

love, 🌘

text:
dikur dikush me pyeti: " cili eshte personi qe adhuron?" dhe une pa u menduar aspak ju pergjigja: " e thjeshte. vetja ime." qartazi vura re habi ne syte e tij. sa here me bejne kete pyetje, i jap gjithmone te njejten pergjigje dhe gjithmone marr te njejtat shikime, te njejtat reagime. degjojme kudo te thuhet qe duhet te duam veten mbi te gjitha, por kur japim prova te tilla te gjithe nxitojne te na quajne egoiste e siperfaqesore. ky post eshte per te gjithe femrat e forta qe e dine kush jane dhe qendrojne me koken lart perpara nje shoqerie qe gjithe kohes synon ti ul. vazhdoni keshtu. jeni frymezim❤

text:
who would've thought, all those years ago when i was a youngster of 19, that i would be running ultra marathons and climbing summits in the italian alps when i was 48. 
not me. 
i didn't think i was 'sporty'. without even realising it i had put myself into a box. categorised myself as one thing, not another. 
the 'brainy one' of the family. so then clearly not the sporty one. 
yet nobody told me that. 
at some young age i just assumed it about myself. 
how often do you put yourself into a box? 
unconsciously limit who you are,  and what you might like to do, by default? 
not based on your talents. not based on your experiences. 
but based on an unspoken, unconscious belief that if you are 'this' then you must not be'that'? because 'that' isn't compatible with 'this'. the hell it's not. 
don't be put in a box. 
least of all by yourself. 
i still have that dress from when i was 19. it was my mother's. 
a fond reminder for that 19 year old how far she has come, grown and expanded (a little too much to still fit the dress 😆😜) nearly 30 years later. 
look back darling. 
how far have you come? 
what are you doing now that you didn't realise you could accomplish? 
the best thing is... it's not over! 
you can keep discovering until your last breath. 
#youaremorethanyouimagine #youneverknow #youneverknowuntilyoutry #listentoyourheart #letyourselfdream #thinkoutsidethebox #untameable #nothingsimpossible

text:
happy national pupusa day from @thefoodmarketchiswick in london where french chef arthur ladriere, the founder of @quinta_food, is cooking up the salvadoran streetfood staple of pupusas for a long line of customers.

these tasty corn dough tortillas are the national dish of el salvador and are traditionally stuffed with classic combinations of cheese and beans, squash, chicharrones (pork rinds), or jalapeños.

arthur has come up with his own version featuring chili con carne (ground beef) for the brits who need their beef fix.

qué viva el salvador!

qué viva la pupusa!

a medical review of adolescents with sexually acquired hiv in jamaica has found that the majority had their first sexual experience between 10 and 14 years old, but in some cases children as young as five years old have also been infected.

this reality is troubling for senior resident in paediatric medicine at the bustamante hospital for children, dr kadene orrigio, who conducted a clinical epidemiology of sexually acquired hiv in adolescents in jamaica between 2003 and february 2017.  read full article here

text:
oh hey! surviving me has its commercial release today on www.sectionii.com! $1 of every purchase goes to the nonprofit @morethanmeorg which builds schools for girls in liberia. 
surviving me was made by women pictured is composer liz lysinger (left), actor mira furlan (center), and writer-director leah yananton (right) at our world premiere at the arclight hollywood in the hollywood film festival. www.sectionii.com is also a platform by and for women & #lgbtq filmmakers & audiences. 
surviving me: the nine circles of sophie (105 min) written & directed by #leahyananton stars #mirafurlan (lost), #vincentpiazza (boardwalk empire), #fredriclehne (greatest showman) and #christineryndak as sophie. 
as she enters her junior year of college, aspiring poet sophie (christine ryndak) embarks on a journey of self-discovery with her friends jimmy (vincent piazza) and kiera (leah yananton), but her moral compass is challenged while she’s trying to study and find a way to pay for her college expenses. as financial and peer pressures suffocate and literally starve sophie, her intellectual mentor, professor slateman (fredric lehne), provides a ray of hope. meanwhile, slateman’s wife, jacqueline slateman (mira furlan) seems to take her husband’s pupil under her wing, further increasing sophie’s sense of confusion. sophie’s eventual choices lead her deeper into dante’s inferno ending with horrific repercussions. but was she to blame? 
surviving me features a brave, luminous performance by newcomer christine ryndak as a young woman awakening to her sexual identity and accepting the weight of accountability as she navigates the “inferno” of sex and love in college. first time filmmaker leah yananton cleverly interweaves poetry and text throughout the story, mirroring sophie’s internal and external struggles.

text:
have you ever asked yourself how you needed to dress up in the morning ? ⠀
⠀
no, not how you wanted to dress up. 
how you needed to dress up. 
i have. 
do you know why ? 
because we live in a world where 100% of women have been a victim of street harassment.
and you know the worst part ? 
we blame women for it. 
we tell them they should not have provoked him. 
when all they are guilty of, was wearing an outfit they liked. 
the outfit is not even the problem. 
i have been harassed wearing a skirt. 
i have also been harassed wearing a huge sweater & a tracksuit. 
we don’t need to change. 
men need to behave ✋🏼
___________________________________________
vous vous êtes déjà demandées comment vous deviez vous habiller le matin ? ⠀
⠀
non, pas comment vous aimeriez vous habiller. 
comment vous deviez vous habiller. 
ça m’est arrivé. 
vous savez pourquoi ?
parce qu’on vit dans un monde où 99% des femmes sont victimes de harcèlement de rue. 
et vous savez le pire ?
on blâme les femmes pour cela. 
on leur dit qu’elles n’auraient pas dû le provoquer. 
quand tous ce dont elles étaient coupables, c’est d’avoir mis une tenue qui leur plaisait.

.

text:
поздравляю! серия селфи закончилась. теперь можно будет лицезреть не только моё лицо

кстати, это фото было сделано после того, как я проспала целый день по приезду в россию. меня шатало три дня. а потом как-то адаптировалась

как ни странно, по прибытию в китай такого не было

не пугайтесь красных глаз, я уснула в линзах и сама тому не была рада (для тех, кто в танке: это ужасные ощущения для глаз)

с любовью,
карина

p.s.: когда-нибудь моя рука отлипнет от лица

text:
we finished the full translation of the so film france interview with rob. as it is quite lengthy we will post it in nine parts. part 9, the last one, is about change. swipe through the next (2) pages to read the full answers.

about change in hollywood: "already people around me are often talking about the metoo movement. within the film business everyone is trying to reach other audiences and now that there are more channels where we can broadcast what we are creating, it extends the spectrum of the kinds of projects that can be realized." about change in london: "i do not remember the last time someone told me he was a poet. it did not happen anymore, but it comes back. so i will go to open mic poetry nights." thanks to our affiliate pattinson art work and @/robspromo twitter for helping with the translations. it would not have been possible without you girls!

text:
how fine is the line between self love and narcissism? is there even a line? 
today was a perfectly normal day. brushing my teeth, doing some homework, checking my phone a couple of times. at around 1:30, i decided that i wanted to go out. after doing my makeup, i looked in the mirror. i thought i looked pretty good. is there anything wrong with that? no. there is a huge gap between self love and narcissism. a person can think they're beautiful without making them narsisstic. self love is so important and it shows that you actually care about yourself. so if you ever find yourself loving how you look, don't ever feel ashamed of it. because you do look beautiful. it's a fact. so there's nothing wrong with thinking that
.
.
.
don't forget to vote in my story! i'd love to know what you think about this
.
.
.
i feel beautiful by fantasia barrino
.
.
.

how fine is the line between self love and narcissism? is there even a line? 
today was a perfectly normal day. brushing my teeth, doing some homework, checking my phone a couple of times. at around 1:30, i decided that i wanted to go out. after doing my makeup, i looked in the mirror. i thought i looked pretty good. is there anything wrong with that? no. there is a huge gap between self love and narcissism. a person can think they're beautiful without making them narsisstic. self love is so impoant and it shows that you actually care about yourself. so if you ever find yourself loving how you look, do not ever feel ashamed of it. because you do look beautiful. it is a fact. so there's nothing wrong with thinking that
.

.

text:
#minggunercerita edisi 11 november 2018

selepas magrib, beberapa perempuan berkumpul membahas soal berita "kontroversional" yang dikeluarkan oleh balairung, pers mahasiswa ugm. "kenapa coba si agni itu keluar malem-malem sendirian, kan bisa nunggu sampai pagi?" "kenapa waktu dua pemuda itu pulang dia ngga minta tolong dianterin aja dan malah milih buat nginep?" "kenapa waktu si hs meluk dia ngga teriak? kenapa harus 'nunggu' dulu?" itu segelintir komentar mereka mengenai kasus agni. 
di satu sisi ada 'keributan' yang terjadi di bawah postingan di line, identitas hs tersebar luas, nama asli, jurusan, nim bahkan hingga nomor orang tua. "sebarin aja informasi soal hs biar dia kapok, ngga malu apa" "kurang ajar, ngga punya otak"

dan berbagai komentar lain soal hs.

kemudian bermunculan berbagai tulisan menanggapi berita agni, mulai dari dukungan atas keberanian agni untuk menceritakan kasusnya, penjelasan mengenai "kenapa agni diem aja pas dipeluk hs", ajakan untuk tidak melakukan persekusi kepada hs, komentar soal sedetail apa harusnya sebuah kasus bisa ditulis oleh media massa, hingga petisi agar ugm mengusut tuntas kasus ini sampai selesai. 
sangat disayangkan bahwa masih ada orang yang menggunakan "namanya juga kucing, dikasih ikan mana nolak" untuk menanggapi kasus ini. 
penggunaan perumpamaan ini jelas salah karena pertama, tidak semua kucing doyan ikan. banyak kucing rumahan yang sejak awal diberi makan makanan kucing sekelas whiskas sehingga tidak tertarik untuk menyentuh ikan. kedua, manusia bukan kucing. mereka punya akal sehat yang membantu untuk memutuskan tindakan mana yang benar dan yang salah. menyamakan manusia dengan kucing sama saja dengan menghina manusia itu sendiri sekaligus menghina tuhan yang telah menciptakan manusia dengan sebaik-baiknya. 
melihat hal ini, pendidikan mengenai gender menjadi penting untuk memanusiakan manusia dan mencegah munculnya pemikiran bahwa si a menjadi superior, dominan daripada si b karena perbedaan gender.

semoga ugm segera menyelesaikan masalah ini sehingga agni mendapatkan haknya dan hs merasakan akibat dari perbuatannya. semoga materi gender segera masuk dalam kurikulum pendidikan di indonesia.

text:
#historical #fiction #novel #bookstagram #girls #metoo #womenssuffrage there are hardly any books written from a woman’s point of view. (they seem to be catching up lately; like why has it taken forever?)
maybe because we had so far to go ... i think the new motto is “where’s the money?” no wonder women have been stifled, abused, have no idols (except singers & stars), because they never had a voice, something (ideas) & someone (in charge) who believed she (the women) could. there are many women in history we simply did not study in class. i say better late than never is a good thing. the girls of our future will simply be empowered! 🇺🇸👩‍⚕️🍎👌♥️

#repost @cocoloveblossom // #happytouchvictoria

we couldn’t recommend this workshop more. betty martin’s wheel of consent is a life changing tool for navigating touch, requests, and desire. corinne is the president of the ssea and an impeccable teacher at the institute for the study of somatic sexology. ・・・
it’s not enough to just be calling our sexual predators and boundary violations. this is the time, we absolutely need a new, nuanced language for consent that includes awareness of systemic and embodied oppression, is trauma sensitive, is pleasure focussed, and simple enough to teach to 10-year olds. i believe we have this tool and we would love to share it with anyone, but especially people who work with people. there is still space in our victoria workshop, dec 1 & 2. dates coming for 2019 in vancouver, ottawa and toronto! 
dm me for more info. sign up at corinnediachuk.com

text:
the #metoo movement in india has been an eye-opener to many. while there is a good chance of the wave crashing soon and losing its momentum, let's make it our personal mission to never turn a blind eye ever again. and most importantly it's imperative that we start a conversation. there is never going to be a 'right time' for it. it will need a lot of effort and care to create/recreate a safe space. so, let's begin! we are stronger together. 
to all the ladies, relentlessly fighting and standing up for the cause - a big warm thank you hug. shout out to- @nairswapna @therestlessquill @mirafmalhotra @kometjuice and many others🙏 .

text:
outside the matrix : the salt of the earth

matthew 5:13-16
13 “you are the salt of the earth. but if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again?

the scripture says you are the salt of the earth. salt is most commonly used to flavor foods. it can overpower the taste of whatever food it is applied to. in terms of the scripture it means our culture is the salt of the earth. african american culture sets trends all over the world. i will focus on music not sports.

like a kitty licking bulldagger that mimics the negative traits of masculinity, these nations do the same. for example, dykes will dress as men but act like the thug men, sagging their pants, talking slow and cool and getting tats.

you rarely see dykes perpetrate the positive aspects of masculinity, because they only mimick what is pushed on them visibly. the other nations do the same thing, they will mimick the thug image of blacks, not the positive images, because they aren't shown that on their televisions.

this is why the scripture says "but if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again", because  we are showing the negative examples. the reality is the history of our people are a righteous people, of great character, great morales and great spirituality. we once were the salt of the heart showing the world righteousness, science and discipline.

hence the common white shaming tactic "we wuz kangz". america has portrayed black men as "thugs and rappers" for generations. so much to the point that urban clothing, tattoos, baggy clothes, cars with big rims, gold teeth and most importantly hip hop/rap is what many people associate blacks with.

when you look at these other nations, they are mimicking the same "culture" that we were demonized with.

when you look at these clips, understand these are smaller examples of larger communities in those countries.

we can go to most countries, in europe, asia and african and see people perpetrating so called "black urban culture". can we go into any predominately black area in america and see black men acting, speaking, dressing or mimicking music and cultures from india, china, japan, korea, pakistan, saudis?
name: PROFESSOR MGTOW
tweet_full:

matthew 5:13-16
13 “you are the salt of the earth. but if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again?

the scripture says you are the salt of the earth. salt is most commonly used to flavor foods. it can overpower the taste of whatever food it is applied to. in terms of the scripture it means our culture is the salt of the earth. african american culture sets trends all over the world. i will focus on music not sports.

like a kitty licking bulldagger that mimics the negative traits of masculinity, these nations do the same. for example, dykes will dress as men but act like the thug men, sagging their pants, talking slow and cool and getting tats.

you rarely see dykes perpetrate the positive aspects of masculinity, because they only mimick what is pushed on them visibly. the other nations do the same thing, they will mimick the thug image of blacks, not the positive images, because they are not shown that on their televisions.

this is why the scripture says "but if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again", because  we are showing the negative examples. the reality is the history of our people are a righteous people, of great character, great morales and great spirituality. we once were the salt of the heart showing the world righteousness, science and discipline.

hence the common white shaming tactic "we wuz kangz". america has portrayed black men as "thugs and rappers" for generations. so much to the point that urban clothing, tattoos, baggy clothes, cars with big rims, gold teeth and most importantly hip hop/rap is what many people associate blacks with.

when you look at these other nations, they are mimicking the same "culture" that we were demonized with.

when you look at these clips, understand these are smaller examples of larger communities in those countries.

we can go to most countries, in europe, asia and african and see people perpetrating so called "black urban culture". can we go into any predominately black area in america and see black men acting, speaking, dressing or mimicking music and cultures from india, china, japan, korea, pakistan, saudis?

text:
folk frågar mig aldrig om övergreppen. om det handlar om att inte såra, rädsla för att skapa en dålig stämning eller för att de helt enkelt inte tror på skadorna för att dom nu läkt och för att såren sedan länge blekts bort vet jag ej. det enda jag vet att det sårar mer att aldrig bli frågad. ständigt bli åsidosatt och att bli bemött med tystnad. är det verkligen så skrämmande att kanske behöva se en människa gråta? vore de inte vackrare att väcka tillit och styrka i en vänskapsrelation eller parrelation istället för att ha en ytlig bekantskap eller vänskap där allvarligare samtalsämnen inte är aktuella.

#intedinhora #metoo #duäraldrigensam 🌹

#citizensofthegray had a succeful opening night yesterday and we're glad to see so many familiar faces of @actorsslash producers  collaborating in front and behind the stage of this production of @teatrodramma by @eliakschneider.perorming in nyc until november 25 at the theater for the new city. 
go support them this  sunday and every weekend! visit www.citizensofthegray.com or @teatrodramma bio for more information. 
sending best vibes to the whole team an especially to our friends actors slashers @julibetancourth, @tony.duran.752,
@hasifffadul 
@ross_rub .

#repostsave @teatrodramma with @repostsaveapp ・・・ we would like to invite you to come see our play today at 8:00pm and tomorrow sunday at 3:00pm 
it is a experimental, avant garde and surreal performance. we use a combination of sounds, movement and music. citizens of the gray or this dark thing that sleeps in me is a theatrical production generated by the curiosity of how the relationship between man and woman has evolved throughout the years and how this relationship has become a struggle for power; a fight to death where there can be only one winner. 
the play portrays a world which is deeply correlated with the the #metoo movement!

there is no dialogue, nor text in this play. it traspases  language  barriers in such a way that any person from any country can understand it, given its universal codes.

at the theater for the new city, ny. 
dates: nov. 9th-25th

visit: https://bit.ly/2nfevgd to get your tickets now.

www.citizensofthegray.com
.

text:
comfort women were women and girls forced into sexual slavery by the imperial japanese army in occupied territories before and during world war ii

acknowledging and prosecuting those responsible is required, but so are full and effective reparations for victims and comprehensive reforms to address the discrimination against women and girls in society that underpins the crimes.

providing justice for the survivors of the military sexual slavery matters not only as a moral obligation but for what it says about our society now and in the future. addressing these past human rights violations will contribute to improving the situation of women and minorities today as well help stop any repetition of these abhorrent crimes.

there are many strong women who are forgotten during the world wars. it’s important we remember them and provide them with the justice and voice they deserve . many ex comfort women are still alive and unmarried due to the torture they experienced . #neverforget #oursister

text:
det finns en farlig tendens att tro att det är en viss ”sorts” män som är de som våldtar, tafsar, skämtar olämpligt, tar för mycket plats, och allt det där som feminismen kritiserar. att det finns vissa män som är ”dom”. men att det också finns ”vi” - vi som är ”the good guys”. jag har upplevt det från feministkillar, de som ju har fattat så de kan ju inte vara en del av problemet. jag har upplevt det från ”snälla killar” som ju aldrig har menat något illa. och jag har upplevt det från frikyrkomän, de som ju värderar det goda samtalet, mjuka värden och absolut inte är såna som kan vara del av orsaken till #metoo, eller andra patriarkala problem. 
problemet är att den som tror den är en av ”the good guys” och immun mot att bli en av ”dom” också lätt blir blind för sitt eget beteende. det blir svårt att ta kritik om en gör patriarkala missar, för” jag är ju inte sån”. det är livsnödvändigt att våga se att - ja - alla män (och ja, även många kvinnor) bär patriarkala strukturer inom sig. ja - det gäller även killar jag gillar. för att kunna prata om dessa strukturer på ett hållbart sätt krävs att våga se att det inte finns ett vi och ett dom. inga är dom andra. så, alla ni fina fantastiska snälla feministiska killar - vi behöver inte höra er beskriva varför just ni är feminismens drömmän. om ni tycker feminismen är viktig - fortsätt lyssna, fortsätt att ödmjukt  och ärligt vara öppna för att utvecklas, fortsätt fråga ibland om ni missar något, fortsätt göra era sammanhang feministiska, fortsätt utmana varandra att vara goda krafter. gör det lättare för oss som gillar er och vill er väl att våga säga till när ni gör något som blir fel. du har inte plötsligt blivit ”dom” - du är fortfarande vi som tillsammans faktiskt kan kämpa för ett jämställt samhälle.

text_retweet:
#repost @facesofbengaluru "i knew of his family’ practices.  he had once justified beating women by saying, ‘if a woman doesn’t listen to her husband, it is okay to hit her. even my father hits my mother when she does mistakes. in fact, a man is mean only when he’s truly in love.’ he was extremely influenced by cinema. he thought behaving like a goon, made him ‘heroic’. he’d say it aloud, ‘yes i’m a bad guy, yes i’m psycho, yes i will hurt you, but that’s because i love you.’"
.
"this one time on my 18th birthday, my friends and he surprised me. it was at that studio bar in orion mall. they were all drinking and my best friend obviously asked me to drink. i hadn’t drank before. he too passed a glass with a smile. and he suddenly turned to me, his smile flattened into a line and he said under his breath, ‘if you touch it, you’re dead’. and then he pretended to be a jovial guy when he turned towards the others. that was my first encounter with the psycho in him."
.
“i thought of leaving him several times as i was losing my sanity. but he’d convinced me that now that he’d touched me, i wasn’t ‘pure’ and that nobody would marry me. i was naive. i was scared that i’d end up alone. i eventually broke up with him and now i’m in love with a gentleman who makes my world a happy place.”
.
“i had a childhood filled with sexual abuse and trauma, just like most other women. i was flat-chested and skinny like every other 8 years old. i stayed at home to be safe. my cousin would come home and slide his hand under my skirt. so if someone asks you to cover and lock yourself in to stay safe, rub my story on their face.”
.
"it is common, but it does not make it alright. today i’m a writer. i write about abuse, shaming, gender inequality and several other issues. i stand up for men, women and people who recognize themselves with the gender of their liking. i am their voice.”
.
“i always told my mother i did not like my name. but now i’ve come to realise that i have been named to know my purpose in life. i want to protect people. i want to be the person i missed having when i faced abuse. by being their voice, by standing by them and making sure no others go through the same.

text:
#boricuasbelike brilliant and #relentless. decolonial bizness world is a free and open method for business education that promotes reparations and decolonization. #reparations means repairing the damage that racism, capitalism, and settler colonialism have produced globally through formal, economic amends. #decolonization means creating open pathways for life to thrive on this planet as we move into the new sun. both reparations and decolonization involve abolishing borders and prisons and restoring the sacred connections between humans and the many other forms of life that live on this planet, earth, as we face #climatechaos, the #sixthextinction, and #proudfascism.

#decolonialbiznessworld is made for the magicians of the global economy, those of us who have been forced to the margins of capitalist accumulation, while serving its masters and everyday beneficiaries. we have been made marginal even as we remain the global majority. decolonial bizness world is also made for our allies, for people who see truth through delusion and violence and are willing to put their money where their mantra lives: on the books and into daily sacred practice.

first, there is no one method or formula for determining reparations.

so much of the violence we experience is personalized. the violence we experience as individuals is always shared by other people and communities, yet how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo.

second, calculating reparations is always an economic and spiritual practice.

above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to create solutions for ourselves and our beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic perspective, what can financial reparations facilitate? #manifestation of #justicia y #sanación.

text:
i fell hard for victoria james, sommelier and partner at cote in nyc, amid animals dangling over bonfires by a dry quarry at an @heirloomfire event @gathergreene. she was with her husband, wine importer @lyle railsback and i was with my husband @barclaypalmer and daughter @sylviepalmer. but that didn't prevent a fairly intense conversation about family, #metoo, challenges to young women coming up in the wine business, alcoholism, the way forward, rosé, and writing. our conversation wandered, rambled, returned, but was always strikingly honesty and direct. victoria didn't scoot around hard topics. i invited her onto #speakingbroadly, so we could delve deeper into the topics we touched upon, including why she hates the word "tender" when it's used to describe young women in the restaurant business; “it means they're young and fuckable." that comment kicked off a provocative interview with one of the country's most celebrated wine talents. listen in for more insights from @geturgrapeon. link in bio.

#women #wine #sommelier #womeninwine #cotenyc #steakhouse #drinking #newyorkcity #metoo #mentor #strongwomen #foodradio #heritageradionetwork

text: today is a day of mixed feelings for me. while i didn’t mention it in any detail in my books, noah and i both come from families with extensive military involvement. noah himself entertained the idea of following the family tradition for a while. honoring and remembering those who have served is complicated while it also brings memories of noah and his family whom i haven’t seen in many years. i usually include them in my annual veterans day activities regardless of the circumstances that transpired between noah and myself because they played a part in my life, even if it was tiny and in passing more than anything else. a #blessed #veterans day, everyone. to read more about the relationship i shared with noah you can purchase my memoir: candy apple butterscotch: a memoir available on amazon now at the #linkinbio👉💻 #fourstars #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor “it’s worth the read it’s about a #woman #empowered and my god that is a #wonderful thing indeed” #linkinbio #authorsofinstagram #independentpublishing #goodreads #newbookalert #readforfree

text:
from @michaelakiersch 
sexual assault and harassment is not only prevalent in the climbing community, it is overwhelmingly frequent. 
in a survey administered by #safeoutside, 1 in 3 participants reported to have experienced some form of sexual assault or harassment. of the women who answered, almost half (47.3%) indicated that they were a victim of some form of sexual misconduct. “after experiencing sexual harassment and assault, 45.4 percent of respondents—and 54.5 percent of women—said the incident changed the way they climb.” this is unacceptable. 
i have my own experience with this in the climbing community. sexual misconduct ranges from catcalling, inappropriate messages, to physical advances. i am not speaking only to those who commit these acts, also to victims, bystanders, and those who are simply unaware. educate yourselves, protect yourselves, and do the same with those in your community. 
we must do better together. link to the full article in my bio. #metoo

text:
"people often ask me why i sew.  when i was younger, i would have said i loved hearing people say ‘i can’t believe you made that?’ don’t get me wrong, i do still love to hear that, but recently i’ve realised it plays a much more meaningful role in my life. a few weeks ago i tried on some clothes in a high-street shop for the first time in months and immediately i felt horrible. why didn’t i fit in the size i should? why doesn’t it look right? why doesn’t it look like how it does on the model? i got back to my trusty sewing machine and took a step back – is it that i don’t fit into society’s expectations of women’s size? or is it more that there are unrealistic expectations about what women should look like? by sewing everything i wear whenever i can, i take back control – the clothes are made to fit me, i don’t try to change my body to fit pre-conceived expectations. in years gone by, girls might have been forced to take sewing classes at school because they weren’t expected to pursue anything else. nowadays, i like to think that sewing is a symbol of empowerment and represents a community of creative women that i feel so grateful to be part of. instead of harshly commenting on each others’ appearances, it’s overwhelmingly positive – we applaud and support each other, recreational sewists and inspiring business owners alike." — izzy 🧵
•
•
•

text:
each day i do at least one thing to work towards fulfilling my dream.  and each day i write in my gratitude journal one thing i am thankful for. today especially, i am extremely grateful to have positive news about my biopsy -  i’m all clear! today will definitely be a special entry in my journal!  i truly believe that everything that happens is all part of my journey.  i’m finding my purpose and it’s so exciting! 
each day is a gift. do something amazing today! even if you’re struggling through life right now there’s at least one thing you can be grateful for. acknowledge it and it will give you the strength you need to keep forging forward! you’re worth it!  xo

text:
i'm over on @feministsof today talking about sewing and feminism 😍 have a read! ・・・
"people often ask me why i sew.  when i was younger, i would have said i loved hearing people say ‘i can’t believe you made that?’ don’t get me wrong, i do still love to hear that, but recently i’ve realised it plays a much more meaningful role in my life. a few weeks ago i tried on some clothes in a high-street shop for the first time in months and immediately i felt horrible. why didn’t i fit in the size i should? why doesn’t it look right? why doesn’t it look like how it does on the model? i got back to my trusty sewing machine and took a step back – is it that i don’t fit into society’s expectations of women’s size? or is it more that there are unrealistic expectations about what women should look like? by sewing everything i wear whenever i can, i take back control – the clothes are made to fit me, i don’t try to change my body to fit pre-conceived expectations. in years gone by, girls might have been forced to take sewing classes at school because they weren’t expected to pursue anything else. nowadays, i like to think that sewing is a symbol of empowerment and represents a community of creative women that i feel so grateful to be part of. instead of harshly commenting on each others’ appearances, it’s overwhelmingly positive – we applaud and support each other, recreational sewists and inspiring business owners alike." — izzy 🧵
•
•
•

repost @hr.memes all jokes aside when it comes to sexual harassment training is key... training is never black and white
training cannot simply comprise the dos and don’ts, the what is and what is not acceptable workplace behaviour, to ensure everyone legally falls into line.
we’re dealing with people here and by nature we tend not to play by the book – situations are never black and white, there’s no heroes and villains, and no two scenarios are ever the same. training therefore needs to mirror this and explore the grey areas, the nuances.  #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
next sunday 11.18, join us for a special event for sexual assault and harassment survivors. we are hosting a restorative justice healing circle to create a safe and sacred space in order to heal from these wounds. within the realm of restorative justice exists a practice called circle keeping which can be used for many reasons, such as building community, learning, peacemaking, healing and conflict transformation. 
a circle is co-created by all participants beginning with an opening ceremony and the construction of a centerpiece created with participants intentions and objects of meaning that have been brought to the circle. next, circle values and guidelines will be built by consensus followed by relationship and trust building involving the sharing of personal stories as sources of wisdom. we’ll then move through some guiding questions that will begin to explore the feelings, concerns and issues as pre-determined by all participants from our previous relationship and trust building, working towards ways we can heal both individually and as a community. a talking piece is utilized to ensure boundaries for those who are speaking and those who are listening and a ceremony is used to close the circle.

our first circle is an opportunity to step into a safe environment, to express your experience should you choose, and to be listened to and held by the other members of the group. in a circle there is no debate, there is no judgement, there is only listening and collaboration via group consent. note, this is a survivor only circle.

the circle will be facilitated by valeria a. gheorghiu and andy izenson trained restorative justice circle facilitators and community uplifters. 3-5pm suggested $10 💕 #restorativejustice #healingcircle #healingtrauma #sexualassualt #sexualharassment #metoo #survivorstories #webelieve #healingtogether #healingeachother

text:
fifth poetry slam of my spoken word poetry series ~ rape 05

lose or thrive dead or alive i want to live not survive
rape is a big deal especially among female victims that should be treated with wisdom
far away from twisted systems
a controversy that leads to shitty policy
a sensitive subject that i will handle with intensive regret
simply explained; it’s having sex with her without her consent or after her disapprovement even if you are her husband
when you drug her rape her and pretend you didn’t hear her disagree
when she didn’t get a chance to interfere?
isn’t she free?
what about powerful rape when they step on the rules and take us for fools
it’s when government sacrifices us for privileges using all sorts of coverages that will eventually turn into public source of rages
let’s talk about gang rape
are you that sex thirsty to play with a girl’s body and take turns?
are you some kind of beasts?
you are monsters worse than predators
i wonder how their wounds can be healed
leaving a scar like that might never disappea
how come we blame girls for having consensual sex before marriage while rapists repeat this rubbish since they’re never punished?
some countries consider rape as deliberate sex if the victim happens to know the assaulter
was the no not an enough reason to penalize this act of treason ?
in some others they marry the girl to her raper hmmm to hide the shame until later (oh! creature)
so genius, now he can rape her legally every day with no blame while she hides her pain under a mere light she remains with no right to fight, this is ridiculous
oh this one is hilarious, if he pays for the date you owe him sex, sounds like every time at this rate.
what’s funnier is that she is the one blamed for her provocative shape
lose or thrive dead or alive i want to live not survive

feminist. dat ben ik. en nog zo veel meer. 
zoveel mensen zijn bang om zichzelf feminist te noemen. “vrouwenrechten zijn wel belangrijk, maar ik wil mezelf niet -jeweetwel - een van die feministen noemen.” feministen zijn geen mannenhaters. willen mannen niet onderdrukken. vraag jezelf af wie er baat bij heeft om het stigma rond het woord in stand te houden. juist. 
vandaag is het nationale vrouwendag. tijd om dat ‘vieze’ woord opnieuw te claimen. laat ons trots zijn om onszelf feministen te noemen. 
#nationalevrouwendag

text:
hoje continua a canção do bandido às 16h30 no teatro da trindade! 
bora!

canção do bandido | ópera
teatro da trindade | 8 a 18 de novembro
qua 19h | qui e sáb 21h | dom 16h30

música & direcção musical nuno côrte-real
libreto pedro mexia
encenação ricardo neves-neves

cantores andré henriques, bárbara barradas, cátia moreso, inês simões, marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça
coro do teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica portuguesa

cenário henrique ralheta
figurinos rafaela mapril 
desenho de luz luís duarte 
assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz

produção executiva força de produção
coprodução teatro da trindade inatel, teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos

partindo do conto tradicional o macaco de rabo cortado, canção do bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado, casanova dos tempos modernos, homem que acumula conquistas e as vai trocando por novas conquistas, sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos. 
o casanovismo e o donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que as guerras dos sexos (ou dos géneros) já não são o que eram, ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes. coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de #metoo? em quem devemos acreditar: no libreto, nos protagonistas, nos antagonistas, ou nas personagens que, falando em vez de cantar, contestam estes diálogos, estes tipos, esta dialética? 
de d. giovanni à música pop, dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense, as personagens de «canção do bandido» trazem para o palco tudo o que lhes ocorre, tudo o que sirva as suas estratégias ou ilustra as suas dúvidas. e os espectadores, certamente, tomam partido.

classificação etária | m12

bilheteira

tel: 213 420 000 
e-mail: bilheteira.trindade@inatel.pt

horário
terça a sábado: 14:00 às 20:00
domingo: 14:00 às 18:00
dias de espetáculo até 30 minutos após o início
segunda: encerrada 
bilheteira online 
https://teatrodatrindade-inatel.bol.pt

text: good morning & happy sunday!! i wanted to take a moment to share a personal experience that has lead to my physical and emotional journey. i was in an abusive relationship on and off for two years. i have just come out of that relationship determined to rebuild my inner (and outter) strength. after surviving cancer and a very toxic relationship, there is a lot of work to be done. the challenge of recovering from a highly critical & abusive relationship is that, your inner dialogue over time becomes your abusers voice. telling you that you are not good enough, you are not worth loving, you are hard to love, you are wrong, you are not a good person. you don’t realize this is happening, but over time, it slowly transitions. eventually you recognize that inner voice belongs to your abuser, and you can recognize it is wrong. nevertheless, it is there and you are forced to listen to it. you hear it criticize you when you look in the mirror, when you make a mistake, when you face rejection, or in situations where you have to think critically. sometimes, it pipes up for no reason at all. it is there to fill you with self-doubt. what i have realized this week is that the more time that goes by without interaction with your abuser, the quieter that voice gets. the less you doubt and second guess yourself. the more confident you feel, and the more ways you recognize that you are in fact worth loving. i firmly believe that with time, my inner voice will be my own again. it will just take time and space. i urge you, to leave someone who is not good for your mental health. you only have one life and we never know when it will be cut short. you deserve a happy and fulfilling life with a partner who nurtures you and magnifies your strengths. god lifts you up with his righteous right hand, and so should your partner 💗🕊🙏🏻🙌🏻 i hope this perspective touches anyone who is experiencing or recovering from abuse. you are so much stronger than anyone will give you credit for. i see you. i believe you. and i truly, truly believe you are worth loving 💗✌🏻 #bbg #mentalhealthawareness #survivor #mentalhealth #depression #anxiety #positivevibes #metoo #selflove #bhfyp #health #wellness

text: #nicedrunkgirlsinbathrooms #womenhelpingwomen #womenlookingoutforwomen sadly i had a few nights where i was able to receive the kindness of strange women and bathrooms. i remember getting sick from having too much to drink one night and women i didn't even know making sure i was okay before i went back out. i always reciprocated and kind it didn't matter what the woman looked like how old she was what she was wearing i saw a woman potentially needing my help. i remember one night in particular at a concert there was a woman who passed out in the mini skirt in the balcony around a lot of guys her friends were kicked out for being drunk and i made a point to make sure security knew that she was by herself vulnerable and drunk. a lot of people were annoyed by her she was young just like i was once and my heart went out to her. i probably prevented her from being raped at night so sometimes when you see those annoying drunk women remember ladies we were once young too sometimes it happens let's look out for each other avoid the next #metoo

text:
it's finally uploaded!! the first ever episode of ptsd tv 😊

what is ptsd tv you ask?! ptsd tv is a place where you can get help on your healing journey from two people who have been in your shoes.

you can watch the 1st episode on youtube. 
we talk open and honestly about ptsd and all it entails. 
how it affected us as individuals and our relationship and how we were able to overcome it 100%

in this episode we're talking about something super important... how to stay positive even in the darkest of times.

this was a huge piece to our healing journey and we know it will help you greatly if you apply these 3 thing too... watch it on youtube: overcoming ptsd

even if you don't believe recovery is possible or that you can do it.. we're here for you and believe in you 100,000%

please reach out if you have any questions or need anything at all!

email me at:
kayleen@overcomingptsd.info

here for you always,
kayleen & brad (& shiloh)

text:
freedom & joy & life & happiness & love
.
here’s me last night feeling all those things going out with the hubs for a little early birthday celebration dinner💃🏼
.
last night was also 6 years to the day that i was going out for the night to celebrate my birthday during my sophomore year of college; the night i was sexually assaulted.
.
every year i wonder how i’ll feel on this day... what will i think about... will it be hard... oh goodness y’all my heart on this day this year is in a place i didn’t know it could be🙌🏻
.
i almost didn’t even realize the day it was until getting ready to go to dinner. i’m so focused on living today and all the exciting life things going on right now that i can’t even bother to let myself sit and play back that night.
.
that night took a lot from me: my confidence; my body; my control; my easy going self; my trust; my sleep; and my “self” in the way i had always known myself to be.
.
but that night has also led to a life that has given me so much more than it took: an education in a field i love; a chance to find out who i am & who i really want to be; a husband who gives me a love unlike any other; a deeper relationship with christ to cling to; a greater passion & ability for living a life of adventure; i am the strongest i have ever been physically, mentally, & emotionally; and my relationship with me, and the love i have for myself, is at a place i used to only dream of it being🖤
.
.
the world can be cruel. bad things happen. evil can be enacted upon us at the hands of others. but evil will never win. .
to put it kindly, i still don’t have very nice feelings about the “boy” who sexually assaulted me. but boy am i a firm believer that the person i have become as a byproduct of the fire i have fought through because of what he did is stronger, more powerful, more faith-full, more joyful, and dare i say more successful, than i used to imagine i would be as i am about to enter my 26th year.
.
my heart will not harden because of the evil others manifest in this world, but instead i will spread love and joy all the more freely in order to give others hope, strength, and a place to say #metoo 🤟🏻

text:
desde batsil queremos hacer un posicionamiento en contra de la violencia hacia las mujeres. 
sólo somos un salón de belleza, pero no podemos ni queremos ser indiferentes, porque nos afecta a todes y queremos contribuir desde nuestro espacio promoviendo una cultura de no violencia hacia las mujeres. 
lo hacemos también con especial dedicatoria, sensibilidad y sororidad hacia las mujeres que nos son cercanas y que padecen violencia de género. estamos con ustedes.

este mes sigue nuestras publicaciones sobre el tema y ayúdanos a compartir el mensaje. #womanempowerment #metoo #hiltonreforma #mexico #cdmx_oficial #urbanacdmx #bellasartes #domingo

text:
cnn anchor don lemon remarked in the same breath monday night that people should not "demonize any one group" in america before saying the biggest terror threat in the country is "white men."⁣
⁣
"i keep trying to point out to people not to demonize any one group or any one ethnicity, but we keep thinking that the biggest terror threat is something else, some people who are marching towards the border like it's imminent," lemon said.⁣
⁣
"we have to stop demonizing people and realize the biggest terror threat in this country is white men, most of them radicalized to the right, and we have to start doing something about them," he added. "there is no travel ban on them. there is no white guy ban, so what do we do about that?"⁣ ⁣@realamericannews

text:
we have a lot to learn from each other. this #sunday we’re reading kate harding’s thought piece in why the intergenerational feminist divide over #metoo is both painful and necessary. here are some key takeaways:
.
.
“young feminists are pushing the growing movement deeper, causing older feminists to worry about preserving the progress we've already made.”
.
.
“feminists of [the younger] generation and older have, for years, been accused of overreacting, of labeling every little touch “sexual assault,” as we attempted to force society to grapple with the existence (let alone prosecutability) of acquaintance or "date" rape.”
.
.
“even if they don't fully realize where it all came from, it's clear that today's young feminists have taken the anti-rape lessons of the second and third waves — only yes means yes, coercion is not consent, consent can be withdrawn at any time — very much to heart.”
.
.
read the full piece at the link in our bio.

text:
отношения с матерью (часть 1)
я могла бы описать их всего в одной истории рассказаной со слов моей матери. она рассказывала её иногда как напивалась; история никогда не менялась, так что думаю это правда: "когда мне сказали "поздравляем, у вас девачка" я не поверила. я попросила, посмотрите повнимательнее, это должен быть мальчик, но мне ответили что нет, это точно девочка. я сказала чтобы тебя унесли, я не хотела тебя видеть. я хотела оставить тебя в роддоме, но забрала из-за давления родственников,  особенно твоей бабушки. я не хотела девочку".
она очень не любила слёзы, я не помню чтобы она сама вообще когда-нибудь плакала. выходила из себя, злилась - очень легко, но не плакала.
если абстрагироваться от моих личных эмоций, я нахожу её человеком довольно легкомысленным и жестоким. мне кажется катастрофичное сочетание. 
в младенчестве она давала мне димедрол растёртый в порошок (сама признавалась когда выпивала) чтобы я спала как можно больше.
в детстве мне не хватало матери, хоть бабушка и занималась мной, что-то такое я чувствовала, как ни крути. 
ничего не изменилось когда она забрала меня. я знаете, терпеть не могу все эти стишки и слезливые цитатки: "мама это ангел", "любите родителей", "мама отдаёт всё своим детям". я сама мама, но даже с этой стороны, не согласна ни с каким подобным утверждением. мама не ангел - она человек, она может любить своего ребёнка, она может ненавидеть его,  она может уставать, быть в отчаянии, мама отдаёт ровно столько, сколько хочет отдавать. 
я любила свою мать.
безоговорочно,  бессмысленно,  я бы могла умереть за неё, я уверенна. мама была моим богом по умолчанию. она не любила меня, но я винила только себя: я родилась девочкой, я плакса, я мечтатель, я рассеянная.... всё я принимала как константу и истину - я ошибка, мама не виновата в своей ненависти ко мне, это я её позор, не оправданные ожидания, разочарование.... и знаете, я могу сказать сейчас примерно то же самое, но с одной поправкой - это не моя вина. 
#7днейвоспоминаний #янебоюсьсказать #акварель #портрет #мама #любовь #жизнь #психология #irinashost #metoo #love #life #psychology #mom #portrait #watercolour #aquarelle #art #instaart
name: Ирина Шост

text:
canção do bandido | ópera
teatro da trindade | 8 a 18 de novembro
qua 19h | qui e sáb 21h | dom 16h30

música & direcção musical nuno côrte-real
libreto pedro mexia
encenação ricardo neves-neves

cantores andré henriques, bárbara barradas, cátia moreso, inês simões, marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça
coro do teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica portuguesa

cenário henrique ralheta
figurinos rafaela mapril 
desenho de luz luís duarte 
assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz

produção executiva força de produção
coprodução teatro da trindade inatel, teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos

partindo do conto tradicional o macaco de rabo cortado, canção do bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado, casanova dos tempos modernos, homem que acumula conquistas e as vai trocando por novas conquistas, sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos. 
o casanovismo e o donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que as guerras dos sexos (ou dos géneros) já não são o que eram, ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes. coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de #metoo? em quem devemos acreditar: no libreto, nos protagonistas, nos antagonistas, ou nas personagens que, falando em vez de cantar, contestam estes diálogos, estes tipos, esta dialética? 
de d. giovanni à música pop, dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense, as personagens de «canção do bandido» trazem para o palco tudo o que lhes ocorre, tudo o que sirva as suas estratégias ou ilustra as suas dúvidas. e os espectadores, certamente, tomam partido.

classificação etária | m12

text:
отношения с матерью (часть 2)
я сейчас оцениваю её с совершенно человеческой стороны. она была изгоем в семье, ей с детства хотелось выделяться, у неё была странная тяга быть лучшей для мужчин; я не знаю корней этой проблемы, но я считаю это было одной из крупнейших причин её самоуничтожения.... я родилась едва ей исполнилось 17!! ребёнок, что могла она дать мне с её странноватым понятием устроиства мира и жаждой свободы. подросток с огромным эго стоящем на пъедестале её красоты. её внешность была её единственной гордостью и инструментом, её не интересовало самообразование, финансовая независимость; в её понимании всё что тебе нужно для достижения целей это красота и умение хорошо тр***ться. я прошу сейчас прощения за моё выражение, но я не нашла других слов для описания этого как есть. это повлияло на мою нелюбовь к красивым, классически красивым, как с картинки, людям. мне нужны несовершенства и несоответствия чтобы влюбиться, чем менее глянцева внешность и глубже (не типичнее) сознание человека, тем больше шансов, что я влюблюсь. и соответственно наоборот. а ещё я должна признать, что до сих пор несу в себе комплекс "я хуже матери". в том плане что я "не красива", "не обаятельна", "не привлекательна", "не сексуальна". я ощущаю себя дешёвкой, в смысле как китайская игрушка. дешёвый неприятный пластик и уродливый дизайн, никаких толком функций, ни полюбоваться ни поиграть. 
она была ужасно ревнива, просто сам факт что я будущая женщина делал меня, ребёнка в её понимании соперницей. соперницей по плану завоевания всех мужчин. всех. могу только догадываться что за травма сделала её такой, но сейчас я чувствую жалость.... ну а с моей стороны, ревность разрушала меня изнутри, когда я видела её интерес к детям мужского пола. я ненавидела каждого мальчика которого она тискала, хвалила, сажала на колени, но и саму себя тоже. я ненавидела себя за то, что я не мальчик. если бы я родилась мальчиком она назвала бы меня адольф или альфред :) адольф шост - как вам?)) #7днейвоспоминаний #янебоюсьсказать #психология #подслушано #портрет #мама #любовь #жизнь #metoo #portrait #life #story
name: Ирина Шост

она была ужасно ревнива, просто сам факт что я будущая женщина делал меня, ребёнка в её понимании соперницей. соперницей по плану завоевания всех мужчин. всех. могу только догадываться что за травма сделала её такой, но сейчас я чувствую жалость.... ну а с моей стороны, ревность разрушала меня изнутри, когда я видела её интерес к детям мужского пола. я ненавидела каждого мальчика которого она тискала, хвалила, сажала на колени, но и саму себя тоже. я ненавидела себя за то, что я не мальчик. если бы я родилась мальчиком она назвала бы меня адольф или альфред :) адольф шост - как вам?)) #7днейвоспоминаний #янебоюсьсказать #психология #подслушано #портрет #мама #любовь #жизнь #metoo #portrait #life #story

! ребёнок , что могла она дать мне с её странноватым понятием устроиства мира и жаждой свободы . подросток с огромным эго стоящем на пъедестале её красоты . её внешность была её единственной гордостью и инструментом , её не интересовало самообразование , финансовая независимость ; в её понимании всё что тебе нужно для достижения целей это красота и умение хорошо тр***ться . я прошу сейчас прощения за моё выражение , но я не нашла других слов для описания этого как есть . это повлияло на мою нелюбовь к красивым , классически красивым , как с картинки , людям . мне нужны несовершенства и несоответствия чтобы влюбиться , чем менее глянцева внешность и глубже ( не типичнее ) сознание человека , тем больше шансов , что я влюблюсь . и соответственно наоборот . а ещё я должна признать , что до сих пор несу в себе комплекс `` я хуже матери '' . в том плане что я `` не красива '' , `` не обаятельна '' , `` не привлекательна '' , `` не сексуальна '' . я ощущаю себя дешёвкой , в смысле как китайская игрушка . дешёвый неприятный пластик и уродливый дизайн , никаких толком функций , ни полюбоваться ни поиграть . она была ужасно ревнива , просто сам факт что я будущая женщина делал меня , ребёнка в её понимании соперницей . соперницей по плану завоевания всех мужчин . всех . могу только догадываться что за травма сделала её такой , но сейчас я чувствую жалость ... . ну а с моей стороны , ревность разрушала меня изнутри , когда я видела её интерес к детям мужского пола . я ненавидела каждого мальчика которого она тискала , хвалила , сажала на колени , но и саму себя тоже . я ненавидела себя за то , что я не мальчик . если бы я родилась мальчиком она назвала бы меня адольф или альфред : ) адольф шост - как вам ? ) )

my therapist started telling me about the dangers of alcohol in august 2016 and at first i didn't believe him. however everything he said made sense and he had not drank alcohol in 50 years. he never had a drinking problem, he just committed to yoga in 1967 when visiting @srf_lakeshrine in l.a.  he learned there how damaging it is to the mind body and spirit connection. eventually i entered treatment for alcohol abuse and learned more about how toxic alcohol is and since getting help have lost the desire to drink. i was lucky and got to spend time at the same self realization center in l.a. during treatment!

text:
ласка которую я получала от неё - насмешки, унижения, оскорбления и побои. если я делала что-то плохо, это было подтверждением что я ничего не могу, если я делала что-то хорошо, это подвергалось критике и насмешке. я была "двоечница" даже если приносила пятёрки, это отбило желание учиться, точнее зарабатывать оценки. если я давала ей повод ударить меня, это не ограничивалось "ремнём по жопе" или подзатылиной, избивала она жестоко, так что невозможно было встать, невозможно было спрятаться, я помню белые искры и тьму перед глазами, думаю тьма - это когда я зажмуривалась, искры - это боль от удара. отчим оттаскивал её от меня если был рядом. мои слёзы и крики были для неё как кровь для бешенного пса. 
моё существование было невыносимо для неё.
а сейчас внимание, вопрос ко всем людям насмехающимся над моими шрамами - откуда же они? наверное безответная любовь в подрастковом возрасте, да?

в общем, эта женщина сбежала с белорусским гастарбайтером когда мне было 12. я жила в одном доме с отчимом.... в какой-то момент меня приютила соседка, смирнова яна (за что я до сих пор чувствую безразмерную благодарность)(кто знает моего отчима, знает, что это был далеко не доброй души человек), но моя мать нашла способ разругаться с ней и мне пришлось скитаться. дальше я боюсь напутать с хронологией и всё переврать со временем, но далее моя жизнь была чередой жизни в притонах с матерью и без неё, сколько раз я убегала от пьяных людей пытавшихся меня изнасиловать, не сосчитать, как много разного рода преступлений я видела и была невольным свидетелем... как я выжила, как я пережила голод, от которого падала в обмороки и не стала одной из тех подростков с которыми мне пришлось иметь короткие знакомства, которые курили, пили и тр...сь как взрослые - я сама не могу поверить. я счастливчик. 
#7днейвоспоминаний #янебоюсьсказать #мама #детство #жизнь #нелюбовь #депрессия #подслушано #metoo #life #love #mother
name: Ирина Шост
